<HL>
   Dividend News:
   First of America Stock Split
</HL>
<DATE>
08/16/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C8
</SO>
<CO>
   FOA
</CO>
<IN>
DIVIDENDS (DIV)
</IN>
<LP>
   KALAMAZOO, Mich. -- First of America Bank Corp. declared a
2-for-1 stock split to be distributed Oct. 19 to shareholders
of record Sept. 21.
   The bank holding company also declared an increase in the
quarterly cash dividend to 30 cents a share, payable Oct. 19
to shareholders of record Sept. 21. The company said the new
payout, after the effect of the stock split, represents a 9%
rise in the quarterly dividend. The split will increase total
shares outstanding to 34.8 million from 17.4 million.
</LP>
